acceptContract().details: Function activates a new contract address as entry point.

acceptDev().details: Function accepts a proposed address for a new dev addition. This dev gets added to the dev array as well as turned as active as default.

addressChange(uint256,string).details: Function outputs the current address proposed as function output to a valid entry contract. The contract will also specify its own name to limit changes on other functions and increase security.

params._percent: percent needed for change to be approved.

boolChange(uint256,string).details: Function outputs the current bool proposed as function output to a valid entry contract. The contract will also specify its own name to limit changes on other functions and increase security.

params._percent: percent needed for change to be approved.

deleteContract().details: Function deactivates an existing contract address as entry point.

deleteDev().details: Function deactivates the active status for a developer.

externalOracleChange().details: Function takes a proposed address value to update the external oracle.

numberChange(uint256,string).details: Function outputs the current uint proposed as function output to a valid entry contract. The contract will also specify its own name to limit changes on other functions and increase security.

params._percent: percent needed for change to be approved.

priceChangeETH().details: Function takes a proposed uint value to update ethereum current price in USD.

priceOfETH().details: Function returns the price of Ethereum in USD

priceOfPair(address,address).details: Function returns relative price of two tokens.

params._buyTokenAddress: address of queried token being bought

returns._0: relative value of token being sold, relative value of token being bought.

priceOfToken(address).details: Function returns the value of the queried token.

proposeAddressChange(address,string).details: Resets all the dev contract votes to false and takes a parameter address as the new proposed change. The string of the function accepting this change must also be parsed in.

params._proposedChange: string cointaining information on permitted function accessing the addressChange function.

proposeBoolChange(bool,string).details: Resets all the dev contract votes to false and takes a parameter bool as the new proposed change. The string of the function accepting this change must also be parsed in.

params._proposedChange: string cointaining information on permitted function accessing the boolChange function.

proposeNumberChange(uint256,string).details: Resets all the dev contract votes to false and takes a parameter uint as the new proposed change. The string of the function accepting this change must also be parsed in.

params._proposedChange: string cointaining information on permitted function accessing the numChange function.

proposeTierChange(uint256,uint256,uint25.details: Resets all the dev contract votes to false and takes multiple params as the new tier proposed. The string of the function accepting this change must also be parsed in.

proposeTokenChange(uint256,bool,address,.details: Resets all the dev contract votes to false and takes a parameter value, status and address of the token. The string of the function accepting this change must also be parsed in.

params._proposedChange: string cointaining information on permitted function accessing the boolChange function.

tierChange(uint256,string).details: Function outputs the current selection proposed as function output to a valid entry contract. The contract will also specify its own name to limit changes on other functions and increase security.

tokenChange().details: Function takes proposed variable values to update token information.

vote().details: Function stores the dev's vote for the current proposed change.

USDpriceETH.details: uint saves the value of Ethereum in USD.

addressProposed.details: List all variables proposed for changes.

contractSupported.details: Mapping key value address (Contract address) returns a bool on contract entry status. True - valid entry, False - not permitted.

devArray.details: Array used to access the address of all developers on Cobalt

devBook.details: Mapping key value address (developer) returns Dev struct information for dev

oracle.details: External oracle instance to provides information on token relative value using other platforms.

tokenData.details: Mapping key value of address (token address) returns the struct with pertaining information on token support and value.

USDpriceETH().notice: Decimals were shifted to the right for more accurate readings on current prices of Ethereum in USD.

priceOfPair(address,address).notice: Fuction checks for token support, if token is not supported, the contract will delegate the task to the outer oracle to pull prices from other sources.

priceOfToken(address).notice: Fuction checks for token support, if token is not supported, the contract will delegate the task to the outer oracle to pull prices from other sources.

vote().notice: We dont limit vote to only active devs as their votes dont get added to the total tally during clearedAction function.
